In this clip, @jessecdraper shares her personal experiences as a woman in tech and finance, including the many rejections she faced and how she used them to her advantage. As a VC, Jesse also has to say “no” to many entrepreneurs. She gives a behind-the-scenes look at her decision-making process and offers advice for entrepreneurs dealing with rejection.  
We also discuss the importance of how we react to rejection, rather than the rejection itself. Check out the full episode (Ep. 134)  in the link in bio!

As we’re thinking about the new year, it’s easy to get caught up in the endless cycle of overthinking our goals and second guessing ourselves. In this clip, @jessedraper shares how her biggest career leaps have been when she had the courage to just go for it.  
What if we just tried it? What if we stopped letting fear hold us back and went for it? Whether it’s a new project, a new hobby, or a new goal, sometimes the only way to achieve it is to just start and take that first next step (as simple as it sounds). So let’s make the most of this new year and commit to trying, even if it means taking a leap of faith and not having everything perfectly in place.  
Who knows what amazing things might happen if we just go for it? 
Full episode available on the Behind Her Empire podcast (Ep.134).

Yesterday we went to the Ocean Rider Seahorse Farm in Hawaii. It was so incredible! We learned so much about sustainable fish farming, aquaculture and what’s killing our oceans. There are 47 kinds of beautiful seahorses in the world and they are all on the endangered species list. Male seahorses sole purpose is to give birth in the seahorse world and the males carry the babies (up to 2000 babies!). So many of these seahorses are being killed along with many other of our ocean friends by things like oxybenzone which is in most of our sunscreen products among other things. Check the ingredients in yours and use a zinc based one instead. Our climate really needs some love and attention right now. We also learned about Seafoodwatch.org which is a guide for consumers to go and help you only purchase environmentally sustainable seafood. Your choices have an impact on the health of the ocean. Let’s protect these incredible creatures and stop overfishing. These are a couple things you can do to help. But if you are in Hawaii, educate yourself by visiting @seahorsehawaii ! @seafoodwatch @montereybayaquarium #climate #aquaculture #ocean

It’s 2023 and women continue to receive only 2% of all venture capital funding. This is a crisis. Halogen VC is changing the trajectory by INVESTING IN WOMEN.

Even though women-owned businesses generate $1.8 trillion in revenue per year, female founders struggle to raise funding. Meanwhile, all-male teams get nearly 80% of venture capital funding. This is not a gender issue. This is a missed financial opportunity. The system is broken.

Over the next 30 days, we’ll be highlighting some of our incredible female founders & statistics we live and breathe everyday to showcase the trillion-dollar opportunity it is to invest in women. From climate change to childcare, our world will look a lot better when it’s more equal.

To kick things off, let’s start the conversation by recognizing investors supporting female founders and flagging them to our female founder community.

👇 Tag an Investor or Founder who’s currently investing or supporting women. Make sure to check back in this feed, where we’ll shout out some of these champions who are the catalysts for putting more money in the hands of women and making big change. ➡️ Tag @halogenvc when you post and use #InvestInWomen.

Let’s change the trajectory and #InvestInWomen together. 

Learn more about how you can join our movement - link in bio.

We wanted to do something more than share the overused statistic in our industry that only 2% of women get venture capital funding. We thought we’d show you some of the faces of the women changing these industries and so many more faces beyond this billboard. Proud to be working alongside women like @sallie.krawcheck who’s changing the way the financial industry looks with @ellevest, women like @jasminecrowe who created a waste management solution that she’s tackling the climate crisis with @goodrco , with women like Jessica Chang who’s solving affordable #childcare with her technology solution @weecare.co working with 55,000 in home childcare locations, with women like Joanna McFarland who’s solving #education and the #transportation gap by getting children across the country to school @hopskipdrive and women like @feliciacurcuru of @bintifamily solving the family crisis by creating a tech solution for adoption that social services agencies in 30 states use now and women like @laurenschultewang who’s giving women more healthy options to use for their menstrual cycle as the largest alternate tampon device player on the market @flex .These are a handful of our incredible companies making change in the world. Get ready for more change to be made by women and join our crusade! I want equality. I was solutions. I want more! What about you? Do you want change? #investinwomen #femalefounders #venturecapital #startups #halogenvc @halogenvc

I tried to be real, honest and transparent about the state of women and solutions we see to increase the itty bitty 2% of VC funding going towards women. I met such incredible power ladies at this conference and look forward to watching them change the trajectory for women too. #halogenvc #jessedraper #femalefounders

Wow. I took my 3 boys to see Barbie this weekend in the theater. I cried. It’s so deep. So beautiful. So real. Greta Gerwig thank you not only for reinventing Barbie but also for the realness you brought about our culture today. Keep making billions for the economy with your art! @mattel congratulations! Please keep leaning into creatives like Gerwig. It’s insane how long it had taken me to get to the theater as it’s been a busy summer. My own father even told me guiltily ‘I feel terrible but I saw Barbie without you.’ When I was 12, my Dad asked what I was into and I said ‘Barbie’ and he taught me about stocks by buying me my first share of Mattel which is still framed on my desk today. Around 2010 I interviewed the ceo of Mattel on my talk show and played Barbie with him. In 2012, Mattel paid me the most I had ever been paid for 3 days of work to launch their new Entrepreneur Barbie and host Barbie’s Fashion lounge for 3 days at Mercedes Benz Fashion week in NY. Thank you for this job @keving & @jamieeohara ! I interviewed everyone from Perez Hilton to pro athletes and celebrities about how Barbie had influenced them. Barbie comes up in more than a few of the speeches on women that I give regularly and I now have a new perspective on it. It’s the first time I have looked back at my former acting career and thought, ‘if only this was the world I lived in back then.’ Thank you to everyone who contributed to getting this film out in the world. If you haven’t seen it yet, you must! This is a historic moment. It was beautiful in every way. I also laughed out loud at the last line. 
#barbiemovie #jessedraper @barbiestyle #girlpower @barbiethemovie

I’m devastated to hear about the death of Supreme Court Justice Sandra Day O’Connor. I have such incredible memories of her. When I was in 5th grade I dressed up as her for a school project. And 11 years ago, she was one of the first women I had on ‘The Valley Girl Show.’ She was a force in more ways than one. I flew to her home in Arizona. I’d had zero sleep and she welcomed me. I usually prepped my guests on what we were going to cover. She said ‘Nope!’ And that was when I realized that if you get a guest like Sandra Day ‘O’Connor, you just let her tell her amazing story. I remember asking to use her bathroom and shaking in my heels because she had this impressive cutting tone when I started to go down the wrong hallway that literally made me jump. ‘DOWN THE HALL AND TO THE LEFT. LEFT!’ . 😂 We did the interview and she gave me these 2 tickets to a museum while I was in town. She was fantastic! Something I’ve never shared before is that before the interview, she asked me about my grandmother. She had known her from living in D.C. when my grandfather worked at the UN. I hadn’t slept and hadn’t eaten and my grandmother who has since passed had struggled with Parkinson’s for 40 years. Sandra asked about her Parkinsons and I guess I just didn’t expect it and I started tearing up. All of the sudden I found myself sobbing and confiding in Sandra Day O’Connor about my grandmother’s struggle with Parkinson’s which to this day, I don’t know that I ever talked about with anyone other than my family. I had to take a minute and pull it together before the interview which is still on the internet today 😂 . I’m honored to have known her. I don’t regret the sobbing but I would likely rethink all the whole lotta leg I showed in this interview. 😂 #JesseDraper #sandradayoconnor #valleygirlshow
